{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"The concrete mismatch is now clear: `getMatchingCoordinates()` explicitly skips any `index.json` entry whose `metadata-version` directory does not exist. Akka’s index points at `2.6.21`, but that directory is absent, so the coordinate is invisible to the gate even though the test project exists. I’m checking whether this library is intentionally “test-only” or if the metadata directory was simply dropped."}}
